		<div class="layout-item-intro">
			<h2>Correspondence</h2>
			<a class="xsmall link-alt" href="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor">Write a Letter to the Editor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>
		</div>

		<div id="article-correspondences" class="correspondences correspondences-collapsed">
								<div class="block-correspondence" id="2707">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>My heart goes out to Jane Bernstein [&ldquo;<a href="/article/1813/">On Regret</a>,&rdquo; December 1996]. I certainly know what she&rsquo;s going through. Our son, George, had open-heart surgery when he was not yet five. The surgeon botched the operation, causing George to have a massive stroke.</p>

<p>Our son is eleven now, and we&rsquo;ve been through many hells. Luckily, he can walk and talk, but it seems likely he will need us to care for him as long as we are able. (I&rsquo;m forty-eight and trying to stay in good health.) Do we have time to finish a sentence? Not for a while now. We&rsquo;ve learned to abbreviate.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Tom Prior<br>Haiku, Hawaii</p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

					</div>

			</div>
    
